            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18100919-73-person653">
                  THOMAS 
                  WOOD
               <interp inst="t18100919-73-person653" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100919-73-person653" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100919-73-person653" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18100919-73-viclabel401" type="occupation">publican</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100919-73-victim652 t18100919-73-viclabel401"></join> at the <placeName id="t18100919-73-crimeloc402">Black Dog, Kingsland Road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18100919-73-crimeloc402" type="placeName" value="Black Dog, Kingsland Road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18100919-73-crimeloc402" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100919-73-off399 t18100919-73-crimeloc402"></join>. The prisoner was a lodger of mine, he was in the habit of opening and shutting the shop. On the 28th of August, between six and seven in the morning, he came down and knocked at the chamber door, he told me the time of the morning, I dressed myself, came down and unlocked the bar, I observed the fastening of the bar had been taken out, I had fastened it myself before I went to bed; I went to the till where I had the over night put two pounds worth of copper, I missed seven shillings and nine-pence, they were marked, the prisoner opened the house for me, he called for a pint of porter, his friend 
               <persName id="t18100919-73-person654">
                  William 
                  Baker
               <interp inst="t18100919-73-person654" type="surname" value="Baker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100919-73-person654" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100919-73-person654" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             paid for it, three half-pence out of the five were marked, the prisoner had another pint of porter, and paid me, two out of the five half-pence were marked, I went to Armstrong, he came and searched the prisoner, he found only two half-pence marked in his pocket, he searched his apartment, the prisoner then said I am the thief, I will show you where it is, and between the bed and the sacking produced a bag of copper, the whole of which were marked except one halfpenny.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in his defence, called three witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18100919-73-verdict403" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18100919-73-verdict403" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 33.</p>
